Description:
Life on the Murray River
Enjoy the spectacular views, walking tracks and wildlife along the Murray River whenever you please with this family home located on the banks of the river, in a quiet corner of town. The kitchen includes a dishwasher, ample storage, gas cookers and a dining area connected to an open lounge room. The gas heating will keep you warm in the winter and evaporative cooling keeps the house cool throughout summer. There are 3 bedrooms, with the scope to use the renovated garage as a 4th bedroom or second living space. The two bathrooms have been recently renovated, and the house creates a relaxed, comfortable and modern atmosphere.
The front garden has been designed to include many native plants that encourage bird life as well as having large trees that provide summer shade with an automatic irrigation system to make maintenance easy. Stepping out the backdoor takes you to a large outdoor undercover living area, with a newly built Red Gum deck, lined with bamboo. The secure backyard is fully fenced offering a carport, workshop/shed with power, and garden shed. The large block allows space for growing vegetables, creating a play area for children and/or whatever you desire.
If you are looking for a spacious home and yard, in a desirable location with proximity to outdoor activities and town facilities, don't let this gem on the Murray slip through your fingers.
